txt.en:
'Adventurer, might I trouble you for your help?

'I must gather pelts for the people in need here in Urash Dâr. Many are fleeing from these Orcs pouring from the demon-pits. I have given them what I could, but it has not been enough. I am in need of more pelts from the jackals, but it is now a task too dangerous for a trader such as myself to accomplish alone.

'I ask of you to bring me any pelts you manage to gather. The jackals can be found to the west, in Urgudag, and to the east, in Khazâda.'
Bring the jackal pelts back to Munsubur in Ub Nishir near Maurûsh.
Munsubur has asked you to help him to gather pelts from jackals in Urash Dâr.
Return to Munsubur with the pelts

'You have returned and with the pelts in hand!'

You give Munsubur the jackal pelts.

'I can not thank you enough, adventurer. These pelts will help many during the cold nights as long as get them to those in need. The other traders here are unhappy with me for not making any coin with these pelts.'
Return to Munsubur with the pelts
Gather jackal pelts for Munsubur from the nearby jackal dens of Urgudag or Khazâda.
